      <Docs>
        <summary>Gets or sets a value that specifies whether preconfigured default settings should be used to configure the <see cref="T:Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting.HostApplicationBuilder" /> instance.</summary>
        <value>
          <see langword="false" /> to configure the <see cref="T:Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting.HostApplicationBuilder" /> instance with preconfigured default settings; <see langword="true" /> to disable the use of default settings.</value>
        <remarks>
          <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[

## Remarks

Setting this property to `false` has a similar effect to calling <xref:Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting.HostingHostBuilderExtensions.ConfigureDefaults(Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting.IHostBuilder,System.String[])>.

The following defaults are applied to the <xref:Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting.IHostBuilder>:

* Set the <xref:Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting.IHostEnvironment.ContentRootPath> to the result of <xref:System.IO.Directory.GetCurrentDirectory>.
* Load <xref:Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration.IConfiguration> from "DOTNET_" prefixed environment variables.
* Load <xref:Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration.IConfiguration> from 'appsettings.json' and 'appsettings.[<xref:Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting.IHostEnvironment.EnvironmentName>].json'.
* Load <xref:Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration.IConfiguration> from User Secrets when <xref:Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting.IHostEnvironment.EnvironmentName> is 'Development' using the entry assembly.
* Load <xref:Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration.IConfiguration> from environment variables.
* Load <xref:Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration.IConfiguration> from supplied command line arguments.
* Configure the <xref:Microsoft.Extensions.Logging.ILoggerFactory> to log to the console, debug, and event source output.
* Enables scope validation on the dependency injection container when <xref:Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting.IHostEnvironment.EnvironmentName> is 'Development'.

          ]]></format>
        </remarks>
